-- Sacyr’s Somague Is Interested in Aguas de Portugal, Valor Says
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2012-07-18T12:17:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-18/sacyr-s-somague-is-interested-in-aguas-de-portugal-valor-says.html
Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV) ’s Somague unit
is interested in buying Portuguese state-controlled water
utility Aguas de  Portugal  SGPS SA, Valor reported, citing Pedro
Cardoso Alves, a director of Somague’s environment division.  Alves said he considers the sale of Aguas de Portugal won’t
take place this year, according to the Brazilian newspaper.  Madrid-based Sacyr is a Spanish construction company.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
